00:00:01.170 --> 00:00:03.820
America is a tapestry of different cultures,

00:00:03.820 --> 00:00:06.850
ethnicities, races, religions, and identities.

00:00:06.850 --> 00:00:08.910
Despite the divisive moment, most,

00:00:08.910 --> 00:00:11.640
Americans see our diversity as a superpower,

00:00:11.640 --> 00:00:14.070
the strength that sets us apart from other nations

00:00:14.070 --> 00:00:14.970
in the world.

00:00:14.970 --> 00:00:17.160
In our new series Our American Village,

00:00:17.160 --> 00:00:20.010
we go inside diverse communities across the country

00:00:20.010 --> 00:00:23.280
to show that there is more than one way to be American.

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:25.980
Today we introduce you to Brooklyn bakery owner Darrell

00:00:25.980 --> 00:00:26.480
Darwoord.

00:00:26.480 --> 00:00:31.670
[MUSIC]

00:00:31.670 --> 00:00:33.500
I'm Darrell Oswell Christopher.

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:38.150
I've owned this establishment, Doc's Cake Shop, since 2012.

00:00:38.150 --> 00:00:39.290
This dried banana pudding.

00:00:39.290 --> 00:00:40.550
Have you had it?

00:00:40.550 --> 00:00:43.740
Yeah, it's ridiculous.

